name: Equipment
definitions: devices that serve all or part of the building and may include electric power, lighting, transportation, or service water heating, including, but not limited to, furnaces, boilers, air conditioners, heat pumps, chillers, water heaters, lamps, luminaires, ballasts, elevators, escalators, or other devices or installations.

name: Breaker_Panel
definitions: Breaker Panel distributes power into various end-uses.

name: Bus_Riser
definitions: Bus Risers are commonly fed from a switchgear and rise up through a series of floors to the main power distribution source for each floor.

name: Disconnect_Switch
definitions: Building power is most commonly provided by utility company through a master disconnect switch (sometimes called a service disconnect) in the main electrical room of a building. The Utility Company provided master disconnect switch often owns or restricts access to this switch. There can also be other cases where a disconnect is placed into an electrical system to allow service cut-off to a portion of the building.

name: Energy_Storage
definitions: Devices or equipment that store energy in its various forms

name: Battery
definitions: A container that stores chemical energy that can be converted into electricity and used as a source of power

name: Inverter
definitions: A device that changes direct current into alternating current

name: Motor_Control_Center
definitions: The Motor Control Center is a specialized type of switchgear which provides electrical power to major mechanical systems in the building such as HVAC components.

name: PlugStrip
definitions: A device containing a block of electrical sockets allowing multiple electrical devices to be powered from a single electrical socket.

name: Switchgear
definitions: A main disconnect or service disconnect feeds power to a switchgear, which then distributes power to the rest of the building through smaller amperage-rated disconnects.

name: Transformer
definitions: A Transformer is usually fed by a high-voltage source and then steps down the voltage to a lower-voltage feed for low-voltage application (such as lights). Transformers also can step up voltage, but this generally does not apply to in building distribution.

name: Elevator
definitions: A device that provides vertical transportation between floors, levels or decks of a building, vessel or other structure

name: Fire_Control_Panel
definitions: A panel-mounted device that provides status and control of a fire safety system

name: Furniture
definitions: Movable objects intended to support various human activities such as seating, eating and sleeping

name: Gas_Distribution
definitions: Utilize a gas distribution source to represent how gas is distributed across multiple destinations

name: HVAC
definitions: See Heating_Ventilation_Air_Conditioning_System

name: AHU
definitions: Assembly consisting of sections containing a fan or fans and other necessary equipment to perform one or more of the following functions: circulating, filtration, heating, cooling, heat recovery, humidifying, dehumidifying, and mixing of air. Is usually connected to an air-distribution system.

name: RTU
definitions: see Rooftop_Unit
Packaged air conditioner mounted on a roof, the conditioned air being discharged directly into the rooms below or through a duct system.

name: Rooftop_Unit
definitions: Packaged air conditioner mounted on a roof, the conditioned air being discharged directly into the rooms below or through a duct system.
see Rooftop_Unit

name: Air_Handler_Unit
definitions: Assembly consisting of sections containing a fan or fans and other necessary equipment to perform one or more of the following functions: circulating, filtration, heating, cooling, heat recovery, humidifying, dehumidifying, and mixing of air. Is usually connected to an air-distribution system.

name: Boiler
definitions: A closed, pressure vessel that uses fuel or electricity for heating water or other fluids to supply steam or hot water for heating, humidification, or other applications.

name: CRAC
definitions: A device that monitors and maintains the temperature, air distribution and humidity in a network room or data center.

name: Standby_CRAC
definitions: A CRAC that is activated as part of a lead/lag operation or when an alarm occurs in a primary unit

name: Chiller
definitions: Refrigerating machine used to transfer heat between fluids. Chillers are either direct expansion with a compressor or absorption type.

name: Absorption_Chiller
definitions: A chiller that utilizes a thermal or/and chemical process to produce the refrigeration effect necessary to provide chilled water. There is no mechanical compression of the refrigerant taking place within the machine, as occurs within more traditional vapor compression type chillers.

name: Centrifugal_Chiller
definitions: A chiller that uses the vapor compression cycle to chill water. It throws off the heat collected from the chilled water plus the heat from the compressor to a water loop

name: Compressor
definitions: (1) device for mechanically increasing the pressure of a gas. (2) often described as being either open, hermetic, or semihermetic to describe how the compressor and motor drive is situated in relation to the gas or vapor being compressed. Types include centrifugal, axial flow, reciprocating, rotary screw, rotary vane, scroll, or diaphragm. 1. device for mechanically increasing the pressure of a gas. 2. specific machine, with or without accessories, for compressing refrigerant vapor.

name: Computer_Room_Air_Conditioning
definitions: A device that monitors and maintains the temperature, air distribution and humidity in a network room or data center.

name: Condenser
definitions: A heat exchanger in which the primary heat transfer vapor changes its state to a liquid phase.

name: Damper
definitions: Element inserted into an air-distribution system or element of an air-distribution system permitting modification of the air resistance of the system and consequently changing the airflow rate or shutting off the airflow.

name: Economizer_Damper
definitions: A damper that is part of an economizer that is used to module the flow of air

name: Exhaust_Damper
definitions: A damper that modulates the flow of exhaust air

name: Outside_Damper
definitions: A damper that modulates the flow of outside air

name: Return_Damper
definitions: A damper that modulates the flow of return air

name: Economizer
definitions: Device that, on proper variable sensing, initiates control signals or actions to conserve energy. A control system that reduces the mechanical heating and cooling requirement.

name: Fan
definitions: Any device with two or more blades or vanes attached to a rotating shaft used to produce an airflow for the purpose of comfort, ventilation, exhaust, heating, cooling, or any other gaseous transport.

name: Cooling_Tower_Fan
definitions: A fan that pulls air through a cooling tower and across the louvers where the water falls to aid in heat exchange by the process of evaporation

name: Discharge_Fan
definitions: Fan moving air discharged from HVAC vents

name: Exhaust_Fan
definitions: Fan moving exhaust air -- air that must be removed from a space due to contaminants

name: Return_Fan
definitions: Fan moving return air -- air that is circulated from the building back into the HVAC system

name: Standby_Fan
definitions: Fan that is activated as part of a lead/lag operation or when a primary fan raises an alarm

name: Supply_Fan
definitions: Fan moving supply air -- air that is supplied from the HVAC system into the building

name: Booster_Fan
definitions: Fan activated to increase airflow beyond what is provided by the default configuration

name: Filter
definitions: Device to remove gases from a mixture of gases

name: Mixed_Air_Filter
definitions: A filter that is applied to the mixture of recirculated and outside air

name: Fume_Hood
definitions: A fume-collection device mounted over a work space, table, or shelf and serving to conduct unwanted gases away from the area enclosed.

name: HX
definitions: See Heat_Exchanger
A heat exchanger is a piece of equipment built for efficient heat transfer from one medium to another. The media may be separated by a solid wall to prevent mixing or they may be in direct contact

name: Heat_Exchanger
definitions: A heat exchanger is a piece of equipment built for efficient heat transfer from one medium to another. The media may be separated by a solid wall to prevent mixing or they may be in direct contact
See Heat_Exchanger

name: Coil
definitions: Cooling or heating element made of pipe or tube that may or may not be finned and formed into helical or serpentine shape

name: Cooling_Coil
definitions: A cooling element made of pipe or tube that removes heat from equipment, machines or airflows. Typically filled with either refrigerant or cold water.

name: Heating_Coil
definitions: A heating element typically made of pipe, tube or wire that emits heat. Typically filled with hot water, or, in the case of wire, uses electricity.

name: Condenser_Heat_Exchanger
definitions: A heat exchanger in which the primary heat transfer vapor changes its state to a liquid phase.

name: Humidifier
definitions: A device that adds moisture to air or other gases

name: Pump
definitions: Machine for imparting energy to a fluid, causing it to do work, drawing a fluid into itself through an entrance port, and forcing the fluid out through an exhaust port.

name: Water_Pump
definitions: A pump that performs work on water

name: Chilled_Water_Pump
definitions: A pump that performs work on chilled water; typically part of a chilled water system

name: Condenser_Water_Pump
definitions: A pump that is part of a condenser system; the pump circulates condenser water from the chiller back to the cooling tower

name: Hot_Water_Pump
definitions: A pump that performs work on hot water; typically part of a hot water system

name: Space_Heater
definitions: A heater used to warm the air in an enclosed area, such as a room or office

name: Terminal_Unit
definitions: A device that regulates the volumetric flow rate and/or the temperature of the controlled medium.

name: FCU
definitions: See Fan_Coil_Unit
Terminal device consisting of a heating and/or cooling heat exchanger or 'coil' and fan that is used to control the temperature in the space where it is installed

name: Fan_Coil_Unit
definitions: Terminal device consisting of a heating and/or cooling heat exchanger or 'coil' and fan that is used to control the temperature in the space where it is installed
See Fan_Coil_Unit

name: VAV
definitions: See VAV
A device that regulates the volume and temperature of air delivered to a zone by opening or closing a damper

name: Variable_Air_Volume_Box
definitions: A device that regulates the volume and temperature of air delivered to a zone by opening or closing a damper
See VAV

name: RVAV
labels: Variable Air Volume Box With Reheat
definitions: See Variable_Air_Volume_Box_With_Reheat
A VAV box with a reheat coil mounted on the discharge end of the unit that can heat the air delivered to a zone

name: Variable_Air_Volume_Box_With_Reheat
labels: Variable Air Volume Box With Reheat
generatedLabel: Variable Air Volume Box With Reheat
definitions: A VAV box with a reheat coil mounted on the discharge end of the unit that can heat the air delivered to a zone
See Variable_Air_Volume_Box_With_Reheat

name: Thermostat
definitions: An automatic control device used to maintain temperature at a fixed or adjustable setpoint.

name: VFD
definitions: An alarm that indicates a loss of water e.g. during transport

Electronic device that varies its output frequency to vary the rotating speed of a motor, given a fixed input frequency. Used with fans or pumps to vary the flow in the system as a function of a maintained pressure.

name: Heat_Wheel_VFD
definitions: A VFD that drives a heat wheel

name: Valve
definitions: A device that regulates, directs or controls the flow of a fluid by opening, closing or partially obstructing various passageways

name: Cooling_Valve
definitions: A valve that controls air temperature by modulating the amount of cold water flowing through a cooling coil

name: Heating_Valve
definitions: A valve that controls air temperature by modulating the amount of hot water flowing through a heating coil

name: Domestic_Hot_Water_Valve
definitions: A valve regulating the flow of domestic hot water

name: Reheat_Valve
definitions: A valve that controls air temperature by modulating the amount of hot water flowing through a reheat coil

name: Return_Heating_Valve
definitions: A valve installed on the return side of a heat exchanger

name: Isolation_Valve
definitions: A valve that stops the flow of a fluid, usually for maintenance or safety purposes

name: Water_Valve
definitions: A valve that modulates the flow of water

name: Chilled_Water_Valve
definitions: A valve that modulates the flow of chilled water

name: Domestic_Hot_Water_Valve
definitions: A valve regulating the flow of domestic hot water

name: Variable_Frequency_Drive
definitions: Electronic device that varies its output frequency to vary the rotating speed of a motor, given a fixed input frequency. Used with fans or pumps to vary the flow in the system as a function of a maintained pressure.
An alarm that indicates a loss of water e.g. during transport

name: Interface
definitions: A device that provides an occupant control over a lighting system

name: Switch
definitions: A switch used to operate all or part of a lighting installation

name: Dimmer
definitions: A switch providing continuous control over all or part of a lighting installation; typically potentiometer-based

name: Touchpanel
definitions: A switch used to operate all or part of a lighting installation that uses a touch-based mechanism (typically resistive or capacitive) rather than a mechanical actuator

name: Luminaire
definitions: A complete lighting unit consisting of a lamp or lamps and ballast(s) (when applicable) together with the parts designed to distribute the light, to position and protect the lamps, and to connect the lamps to the power supply.

name: Luminaire_Driver
definitions: A power source for a luminaire

name: Louver
definitions: Device consisting of an assembly of parallel sloping vanes, intended to permit the passage of air while providing a measure of protection against environmental influences

name: Meter
definitions: A device that measure usage or consumption of some media --- typically a form energy or power.

name: Building_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures usage or consumption of some media for a whole building

name: Building_Chilled_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of chilled water of a whole building

name: Building_Electrical_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of electricity of a whole building

name: Building_Gas_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of gas of a whole building

name: Building_Hot_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of hot water of a whole building

name: Building_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of water of a whole building

name: Electrical_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of electricity

name: Building_Electrical_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of electricity of a whole building

name: Gas_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of gas

name: Building_Gas_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of gas of a whole building

name: Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of water

name: Building_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of water of a whole building

name: Chilled_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of chilled water

name: Building_Chilled_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of chilled water of a whole building

name: Hot_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of hot water

name: Building_Hot_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of hot water of a whole building

name: Solar_Panel
definitions: A colloquial term for a photovoltaic module. A Solar panel is an assembly of photovoltaic cells mounted in a framework for installation that use sunlight as a source of energy to generate direct current electricity.

name: Steam_Distribution
definitions: Utilize a steam distribution source to represent how steam is distributed across multiple destinations

name: Water_Distribution
definitions: Utilize a water distribution source to represent how water is distributed across multiple destinations (pipes)

name: Weather_Station
definitions: A dedicated weather measurement station

name: Building
definitions: a structure wholly or partially enclosed within exterior walls, or within exterior and party walls, and a roof, affording shelter to persons, animals, or property.
An independent unit of the built environment with a characteristic spatial structure, intended to serve at least one function or user activity [ISO 12006-2:2013]

name: Floor
definitions: A level, typically representing a horizontal aggregation of spaces that are vertically bound. (referring to IFC)

name: Basement
definitions: The floor of a building which is partly or entirely below ground level.

name: Space
definitions: A part of the physical world or a virtual world whose 3D spatial extent is bounded actually or theoretically, and provides for certain functions within the zone it is contained in.

name: Room
definitions: Base class for all more specific room types.

name: Laboratory
definitions: facility acceptable to the local, national, or international recognized authority having jurisdiction and which provides uniform testing and examination procedures and standards for meeting design, manufacturing, and factory testing requirements.

name: Cold_Box
definitions: in a gas separation unit, the insulated section that contains the low-temperature heat exchangers and distillation columns.

name: Environment_Box
definitions: (also known as climatic chamber), enclosed space designed to create a particular environment.

name: Freezer
definitions: cold chamber usually kept at a temperature of 22°F to 31°F (–5°C to –1°C), with high-volume air circulation.

name: Hot_Box
definitions: hot air chamber forming part of an air handler.

name: Storey
definitions: A level, typically representing a horizontal aggregation of spaces that are vertically bound. (referring to IFC)

name: Zone
definitions: (1) a separately controlled heated or cooled space. (2) one occupied space or several occupied spaces with similar occupancy category, occupant density, zone air distribution effectiveness, and zone primary airflow per unit area. (3) space or group of spaces within a building for which the heating, cooling, or lighting requirements are sufficiently similar that desired conditions can be maintained throughout by a single controlling device.

name: Fire_Zone
definitions: combustion chamber in a furnace or boiler.

name: HVAC_Zone
definitions: a space or group of spaces, within a building with heating, cooling, and ventilating requirements, that are sufficiently similar so that desired conditions (e.g., temperature) can be maintained throughout using a single sensor (e.g., thermostat or temperature sensor).

name: Fluid
definitions: substance, as a liquid or gas, that is capable of flowing and that changes shape when acted on by a force.

name: Gas
definitions: state of matter in which substances exist in the form of nonaggregated molecules and which, within acceptable limits of accuracy, satisfy the ideal gas laws; usually a highly superheated vapor. See [[state]].

name: Air
definitions: the invisible gaseous substance surrounding the earth, a mixture mainly of oxygen and nitrogen.

name: Building_Air
definitions: air contained within a building

name: Bypass_Air
definitions: air in a bypass duct, used to relieve static pressure

name: Discharge_Air
definitions: the air exiting the registers (vents).

name: Exhaust_Air
definitions: air that must be removed from a space due to contaminants, regardless of pressurization

name: Mixed_Air
definitions: (1) air that contains two or more streams of air. (2) combined outdoor air and recirculated air.

name: Outside_Air
definitions: air external to a defined zone (e.g., corridors).

name: Return_Air
definitions: air removed from a space to be recirculated or exhausted. Air extracted from a space and totally or partially returned to an air conditioner, furnace, or other heating, cooling, or ventilating system.

name: Supply_Air
definitions: (1) air delivered by mechanical or natural ventilation to a space, composed of any combination of outdoor air, recirculated air, or transfer air. (2) air entering a space from an air-conditioning, heating, or ventilating apparatus for the purpose of comfort conditioning. Supply air is generally filtered, fan forced, and either heated, cooled, humidified, or dehumidified as necessary to maintain specified conditions. Only the quantity of outdoor air within the supply airflow may be used as replacement air.

name: Zone_Air
definitions: air inside a defined zone (e.g., corridors).

name: CO2
definitions: Carbon Dioxide in the vapor phase

name: Natural_Gas
definitions: Fossil fuel energy source consisting largely of methane and other hydrocarbons

name: Steam
definitions: water in the vapor phase.

name: Liquid
definitions: state of matter intermediate between crystalline substances and gases in which the volume of a substance, but not the shape, remains relatively constant.

name: Gasoline
definitions: Petroleum derived liquid used as a fuel source

name: Liquid_CO2
definitions: Carbon Dioxide in the liquid phase

name: Oil
definitions: a viscous liquid derived from petroleum, especially for use as a fuel or lubricant.

name: Fuel_Oil
definitions: Petroleum based oil burned for energy

name: Water
definitions: transparent, odorless, tasteless liquid; a compound of hydrogen and oxygen (H2O), containing 11.188% hydrogen and 88.812% oxygen by mass; freezing at 32°F (0°C); boiling near 212°F (100°C).

name: Blowdown_Water
definitions: Water expelled from a system to remove mineral build up

name: Chilled_Water
definitions: water used as a cooling medium (particularly in air-conditioning systems or in processes) at below ambient temperature.

name: Condenser_Water
definitions: Water used used to remove heat through condensation

name: Deionized_Water
definitions: Water which has been purified by removing its ions (constituting the majority of non-particulate contaminants)

name: Domestic_Water
definitions: Tap water for drinking, washing, cooking, and flushing of toliets

name: Hot_Water
definitions: Hot water used for HVAC heating or supply to hot taps

name: Makeup_Water
definitions: Water used used to makeup water loss through leaks, evaporation, or blowdown

name: Solid
definitions: one of the three states or phases of matter characterized by stability of dimensions, relative incompressibility, and molecular motion held to limited oscillation.

name: Frost
definitions: frost formed on the cold surface (tubes, plates) of a cooling coil.

name: Hail
definitions: pellets of frozen rain which fall in showers from cumulonimbus clouds.

name: Ice
definitions: Water in its solid form

name: Alarm
definitions: Alarm points are signals (either audible or visual) that alert an operator to an off-normal condition which requires some form of corrective action

name: Air_Flow_Loss_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates loss in air flow.

name: Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with the temperature of air.

name: Discharge_Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with the temperature of discharge air.

name: High_Discharge_Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates that discharge air temperature is too high

name: Return_Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with the temperature of return air.

name: High_Return_Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates that return air temperature is too high

name: Low_Return_Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates that return air temperature is too low

name: Supply_Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with the temperature of supply air.

name: CO2_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with the presence of carbon dioxide.

name: High_CO2_Alarm
definitions: A device that indicates high concentration of carbon dioxide.

name: Change_Filter_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates that a filter must be changed

name: Communication_Loss_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates a loss of communication e.g. with a device or controller

name: Cycle_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates off-normal conditions associated with HVAC cycles

name: Short_Cycle_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates a short cycle occurred. A short cycle occurs when a cooling cycle is prevented from completing its full cycle

name: Emergency_Alarm
definitions: Alarms that indicate off-normal conditions associated with emergency systems

name: Emergency_Generator_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates off-normal conditions associated with an emergency generator

name: Failure_Alarm
definitions: Alarms that indicate the failure of devices, equipment, systems and control loops

name: Unit_Failure_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the failure of an equipment or device

name: Humidity_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with the concentration of water vapor in the air.

name: High_Humidity_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates high concentration of water vapor in the air.

name: Low_Humidity_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates low concentration of water vapor in the air.

name: Leak_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates leaks occured in systems containing fluids

name: Condensate_Leak_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates a leak of condensate from a cooling system

name: Maintenance_Required_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates that repair/maintenance is required on an associated device or equipment

name: Overload_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that can indicate when a full-load current is exceeded.

name: Power_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with electrical power.

name: Power_Loss_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates a power failure.

name: Pressure_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with pressure.

name: High_Head_Pressure_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates a high pressure generated on the output side of a gas compressor in a refrigeration or air conditioning system.

name: Low_Suction_Pressure_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates a low suction pressure in the compressor in a refrigeration or air conditioning system.

name: Smoke_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with smoke.

name: Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with temperature.

name: Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with the temperature of air.

name: High_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates high temperature.

name: High_Discharge_Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates that discharge air temperature is too high

name: High_Return_Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates that return air temperature is too high

name: Low_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates low temperature.

name: Low_Return_Air_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates that return air temperature is too low

name: Water_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with temperature of water.

name: Discharge_Water_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with temperature of the discharge water.

name: Supply_Water_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with temperature of the supply water.

name: Water_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates water leaks.

name: Deionized_Water_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates deionized water leaks.

name: Water_Loss_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates a loss of water e.g. during transport

name: Water_Temperature_Alarm
definitions: An alarm that indicates the off-normal conditions associated with temperature of water.

name: Command
definitions: A Command is an output point that directly determines the behavior of equipment and/or affects relevant operational points.

definitions: Controls the amount of cooling to be delivered (typically as a proportion of total cooling output)

name: Damper_Command
definitions: Controls properties of dampers

name: Damper_Position_Command
definitions: Controls the position (the degree of openness) of a damper

name: Direction_Command

definitions: Commands that disable functionality

name: Disable_Fixed_Enthalpy_Command

name: Disable_Fixed_Temperature_Command

name: Enable_Fixed_Enthalpy_Command

name: Frequency_Command
definitions: Controls the frequency of a device's operation (e.g. rotational frequency)

name: Max_Frequency_Command
definitions: Sets the maximum permitted frequency

name: Heating_Command
definitions: Controls the amount of heating to be delivered (typically as a proportion of total heating output)

name: Lead_Lag_Command

name: Load_Shed_Command
definitions: Controls load shedding behavior provided by a control system

name: Luminance_Command
definitions: Controls the amount of luminance delivered by a lighting system

name: Mode_Command
definitions: Controls the operating mode of a device or controller

name: Automatic_Mode_Command
definitions: Controls whether or not a device or controller is operating in "Automatic" mode

name: Maintenance_Mode_Command
definitions: Controls whether or not a device or controller is operating in "Maintenance" mode

name: Occupancy_Command
definitions: Controls whether or not a device or controller is operating in "Occupied" mode

name: On_Off_Command
definitions: An On/Off Command controls or reports the binary status of a control loop, relay or equipment activity

name: Lead_On_Off_Command
definitions: Controls the active/inactive status of the "lead" part of a lead/lag system

name: Off_Command
definitions: An Off Command controls or reports the binary 'off' status of a control loop, relay or equipment activity. It can only be used to stop/deactivate an associated equipment or process, or determine that the related entity is 'off'

name: On_Command
definitions: An On Command controls or reports the binary 'on' status of a control loop, relay or equipment activity. It can only be used to start/activate an associated equipment or process, or determine that the related entity is 'on'

name: Start_Stop_Command
definitions: A Start/Stop Command controls or reports the active/inactive status of a control sequence

name: Override_Command
definitions: Controls or reports whether or not a device or control loop is in 'override'

name: Position_Command
